  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Vampiric Casting drawback, bite attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Benefit:</strong> You automatically drain a creature&#8217;s blood (as described by the Vampiric Casting general drawback) as part of any successful bite attack. You may also choose to drain a creature&#8217;s blood as an option made after succeeding at a check to maintain a grapple. When you drain a creature&#8217;s blood, you gain 5 temporary hit points and a +1 bonus on all Constitution-based saves and skill checks for one minute. You may stack the temporary hit points with themselves, up to a maximum amount of 5 temporary hit points for every 3 Hit Dice you possess.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have taken the Vampiric Casting drawback twice, you additionally gain a +1 bonus to all attack and damage rolls with your bite attack for one minute after draining blood, increasing by +1 at 10th character level and every 10 levels thereafter.</p>\n",
